<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-01-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-01-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="30" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d30">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Ewing</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-01-08"><hi rend="italic">January 8,
                                1896</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 189.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to inform you that your dispatch
                            No. 165, of the 19th ultimo, relative to the prohibition of the
                            importation of American cattle into Belgium, has been received.</p>
                        <p>The Department fully approves your note of the 19th ultimo to the Belgian
                            foreign office on the subject.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Olney</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>